'''Claudius Regaud''' (born 30 January 1870 in [[Lyons]], [[France]]; died 29 December 1940 in [[Couzon-au-Mont-d'Or]], [[France]]) was a [[French people|French]] doctor and biologist, one of the pioneers in [[radiotherapy]] at the [[Curie Institute (Paris)|Curie Institute]].

==Scientific work==
In 1906, Regaud discovered that one of the effects of [[X-ray]] treatment is sterility. He deduced that X-rays could also be used against rapidly growing cells other than gametes and, thus, against [[cancer]]ous [[tumor]]s.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.medarus.org/Medecins/MedecinsTextes/curiemp.html |title=Portrait de Médecins |language=French |trans-title=Portraits of Physicians |work=Medarus |accessdate=25 April 2014 |archive-url=https://archive.is/20130910171248/http://www.medarus.org/Medecins/MedecinsTextes/curiemp.html |archive-date=10 September 2013 |dead-url=yes }}</ref> He proceeded to conduct the first experiments in this area.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.lefigaro.fr/mon-figaro/2012/08/10/10001-20120810ARTFIG00445-marie-curie-a-l-origine-de-la-radiotherapie.php |title=Marie Curie à l'origine de la radiothérapie |trans-title=Marie Curie on the origin of radiotherapy |language=French |work=[[Le Figaro]] |first=Anne |last=Prigent |date=10 August 2012 |accessdate=25 April 2014}}</ref> In 1912, at the Curie Institute, he was given responsibility for the Pasteur Laboratory, with the mission to study the biological and medical effects of [[radioactivity]]. The Curie laboratory, in contrast, dealt with research in the fields of [[physics]] and [[chemistry]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://curie.fr/fr/fondation/2009-centenaire-institut-curie |title=2009, Centenaire de l'Institut Curie |language=French |trans-title=2009: Centenary of the Curie Institute |work=[[Curie Institute (Paris)|Curie Institute of Paris]] |date=8 June 2010 |accessdate=25 April 2014 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140725023616/http://curie.fr/fr/fondation/2009-centenaire-institut-curie |archive-date=25 July 2014 |dead-url=yes }}</ref>

In addition, he started a program to fight [[neoplasia]] and conducted research to determine the optimal duration and dosage for radiation therapy.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://musee.curie.fr/decouvrir/exposition-permanente/visite-virtuelle/d2 |title= Claudius Regaud (1870-1940) |language=French |publisher=[[Musée Curie]] |accessdate=25 April 2014}}</ref>

